description:
Spare Parts

It's Night of the Living Decepticon in this issue of TRANSFORMERS Comic! Tumbleweed blows. A coyote howls. The wind whips up the desert sands. A figure shambles out of the dark, groaning... Dead End is falling apart at the cold-riveted seams. And it's a full moon!!

Cut-out TRANSFORMERS standees

There's a cool TRANSFORMERS standee on the reverse of this issue's taller, sturdier, indisputably more awesome outer cover. Just cut it out, choose Autobot or Decepticon, and slot it together! The standee is reversible so you can switch allegiances whenever you like!

Design a TRANSFORMER gallery

TRANSFORMERS Comic's 'Design a Robot' competition seems to have got you all shook up, judging by the responses that came flooding in! You can check out an awesome selection of entries in this issue - and the winner will be revealed in issue #2.12!
name: Spare Parts!

description:
Original Comic Strip: Turnabout

Our all-new comic strip heads towards its thrilling climax in the latest issue of TRANSFORMERS Comic, as Skids and Mudflap discover that being Decepticons is out of this world! The Twins join Soundwave at his headquarters on the moons of Mars, where they have a little job to do…

Sideswipe’s Armoury: Heavy Armour

When it comes to heavy metal hardware, the TRANSFORMERS get some pretty stiff competition from human armoured vehicles. In the latest issue, check out just a few that lined up with the Autobots in the latest blockbuster TRANSFORMERS movie Revenge of the Fallen!

Competitions Galore!

Win the mother of all prizes in the latest issue – an incredible Devastator Action Figure. Plus, win Revenge of the Fallen on DVD, a Nintendo DS and Combat of Giants: Dragons games, Nintendo Wii’s and games including TMNT Mash-up and Rabbids Go Home, and loads more cool gear!

Reprints

  • All Hail Megatron #5b
name: Turnabout; Family Strife!

description:
Brand New Comic Strip #1: Back-to-Back

Skids and Mudflap are snarled up as Soundwave springs his trap on Ransack in the final part of Simon Furman’s epic story. The fight is on!

Brand New Comic Strip #2: All Hail Megatron

It’s the end of the world as we know it! Has Earth really fallen to Deceptions? As the reunited Autobots contemplate a future without Optimus Prime, what now for the troubled Megatron? The Decepticon leader has it all: incredible power; command of an unstoppable army; a shiny chassis. But is he happy?

Reprint

Note: Only portions of each issue were used to complete the story.

  • All Hail Megatron #6, #7, & #9
name: Back-to-Back;  Darkness Fall!

description:
Brand New Comic Strip: Culture Shock

TRANSFORMERS Comic is now a leaner, meaner, greener fighting machine but with all the firepower and hard-hitting action that TransFans know and love. A brand new original comic strip starts in this issue, as Jolt finds a trip to Las Vegas to be an ‘electrifying’ experience!

Sideswipe’s Armoury: Supercarriers

Weighing over 100,000 tonnes, powered by two nuclear reactors, and costing around 4.5 billion dollars to build – they’re the US Navy’s greatest war machines! Find out all about Nimitz-class aircraft carriers in TRANSFORMERS Comic's regular feature ‘Sideswipe’s Armoury’.
name: Culture Shock

description:
Brand New Comic Strip: Bring Me The Head of Optimus Prime

Optimus Prime is used to having Decepticons on his trail, but it seems a bit of a cheek when the Autobot leader finds himself under attack from his supposed allies – human beings!

Character Profile: Soundwave

Orbiting in space miles above the Earth, Soundwave is a living hive mind that sucks up information. Find out all about the Communications Specialist in this issue of TRANSFORMERS Comic, as we bring you all the intel on the Decepticons’ ultra-sophisticated Eye in the Sky!
name: Bring Me the Head of Optimus Prime

description:
Brand New Comic Strip: Rules Of Engagement

This issue of TRANSFORMERS Comic is packed full of metal mayhem - kicking off with a story of the Autobots' newest recruits. Rollbar, Jolt and Dune Runner request some front line action from their instructor, Springer - but it's not long 'til they're mixing it up with Tankor and Dirge!

Way Past Cool: Bumblebee's Game Reviews

Get the lowdown on some of the coolest new games for all the major consoles! Street Fighter is back with eight new characters in Super Street Fighter IV, Tony Stark returns in Iron Man 2 and football fever hits with 2010 FIFA Wold Cup South Africa!
name: Rules of Engagement

description:
Brand New Comic Strip: Inside Out

Venture to South Africa and check in on some Decepticon captives in this issue of TRANSFORMERS Comic! Brawn, Wideload and Smokescreen are on hand to guard the inmates, and protect humanity – but no-one would be foolish enough to try and stage a prison break, right?
name: Inside Out!

description:
Brand new comic strip: Head in the Clouds

Stratosphere is brought down a peg or two in a brand new comic strip featuring in the latest issue of TRANSFORMERS Comic! The high-flyin' Autobot runs into a familiar - and ugly - face, and needs to use all of his wits and cunning to survive the skirmish...!
name: Head in the Clouds

description:
Brand new comic strip: Making Waves

Soundwave enters the realm of the strange when he accidentally stumbles into the Bermuda Triangle. What weirdness awaits the dastardly Decepticon?
name: Making Waves

description: Movie adaptation. Merida is a young Scottish princess, who has a great passion: she's a very skillful archer! When her passion puts too much strain on the demands of her life as a princess, Merida runs away from home and turns to a witch to help her. But the terrible witch casts a spell that may doom Merida and her family, and now the young princess has to use all her courage to break the curse and save her family...and the whole kingdom!

It should have been a quick in-and-out, an easy paycheck for an easy hit. They should have been able to blow in, blow away the little village of green-skinned guys called Skyes, and blow out before anyone knew what was happening. They're the Star Slammers -- they've done it a million times harder a million times before. But when they got there, it was like the Skyes . . . they were waiting. Like they knew someone had put a hit on them. And they were ready to hit back. When it was over, Commander Rojas had become the first Star Slammer ever captured alive! And if the Skyes have their way, he won't stay alive for long!
